content:
Check:
  all:
    - name: QORIG
      operator: non_empty
    - name: QORIG
      operator: not_equal_to
      value: COLLECTED
    - name: QORIG
      operator: not_equal_to
      value: DERIVED
    - name: QORIG
      operator: not_equal_to
      value: OTHER
    - name: QORIG
      operator: not_equal_to
      value: NOT AVAILABLE
Core:
  Id: CDISC.SENDIG.255
  Version: '1'
  Status: Draft
Description: QORIG is used to indicate the origin of the data. Possible values are
  COLLECTED, DERIVED, OTHER, and NOT AVAILABLE.
Outcome:
  Message: When populated QORIG may only have one of the values COLLECTED, DERIVED,
    OTHER, and NOT AVAILABLE
Rule Type: Record Data
Sensitivity: Record
Authorities:
  - Organization: CDISC
    Standards:
      - Name: SENDIG
        Version: '3.1'
        References:
          - Origin: SDTM and SENDIG Conformance Rules
            Rule Identifier:
              Id: '255'
              Version: '1'
            Version: '2.0'
            Citations:
              - Cited Guidance: QORIG is used to indicate the origin of the data.
                  Possible values are COLLECTED, DERIVED, OTHER, and NOT AVAILABLE.
                Document: IG v3.1
                Item: Specification
                Section: '8.3'
Scope:
  Classes:
    Include:
      - RELATIONSHIP
  Domains:
    Include:
      - SUPP--
